# Cloudflare Pages/Workers headers.
#
# NOTE: We intentionally do NOT set COOP/COEP (cross-origin isolation). Isolation
# would enable multi-threaded WASM (SharedArrayBuffer), but it also makes the
# browser reject Hugging Face model files (tokenizer.json, config.json, *.onnx)
# with CORS errors, because that cross-origin CDN doesn't send the resource-policy
# headers isolation then requires. WebGPU (our primary path) needs no isolation,
# and the WASM fallback still works single-threaded — so dropping isolation makes
# model loading reliable. If we later want threaded WASM, self-host/proxy the
# models same-origin and re-add COOP/COEP.

# Vite fingerprints asset filenames, so they're safe to cache forever.
/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
